The paper deals with geometric packing problems, specifically packing anchored rectangles and squares. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and reductions to maximum weight independent set (MWIS), which are topics in approximation algorithms (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and game theory (cs.GT).
